## v2.11.0 (2026-04-27)

**Changed by:** ProjectMnemosyne + 10 HomericIntelligence repos — 34+ PRs rebased (2026-04-27)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Bumped version 2.10.0 → 2.11.0
- Added trigger #29: before rebasing Mnemosyne skill PRs, confirm main CI is green first
  (`gh run list --branch main --limit 3`); rebasing onto broken main cannot unblock PRs
- Added trigger #30: dependabot branches require `git push --force` (not `--force-with-lease`)
  because GitHub auto-rebases between fetch and push, making the lease ref stale
- Added trigger #31: repo only allows squash merge (Charybdis) — `gh pr merge --auto --rebase`
  fails; check with `gh api repos/OWNER/REPO --jq '.allow_squash_merge,.allow_rebase_merge,.allow_merge_commit'`
- Added trigger #32: pixi.lock SHA changes after pyproject.toml conflict resolution — always
  run `pixi lock` before pushing if pixi.lock exists in the repo
- Added trigger #33: Mnemosyne markdownlint `globs: "**/*.md"` in workflow overrides
  `.markdownlintignore`; fix workflow on main first, then rebase all skill PRs
- Added 5 new "When to Use" bullets matching the 5 new triggers
- Added 3 new Failed Attempts rows:
  - `git push --force-with-lease` on dependabot branch → lease stale; use `--force`
  - Rebasing Mnemosyne skill PRs when main CI was failing → PRs remain BLOCKED;
    check main CI first
  - Not regenerating pixi.lock after pixi.lock rebase → `pixi install --locked` fails
- Added Quick Reference commands: check main CI before rebase, dependabot --force push,
  pixi lock regeneration
- Added Verified On row: ProjectMnemosyne + 10 HomericIntelligence repos, 34+ PRs,
  PRs #1447/#1448/#1449 blocked by main markdownlint CI issue

### Why
During a 34+ PR rebase session across ProjectMnemosyne and 10 other HomericIntelligence repos:
1. PRs #1447/#1448/#1449 were blocked not due to rebase staleness but because main's markdownlint
   workflow used `globs: "**/*.md"` which overrides `.markdownlintignore`. Pattern: always check
   main CI before starting a rebase session.
2. A dependabot branch (conan/pyproject version bump) rejected `--force-with-lease` because
   GitHub auto-rebases dependabot branches between our fetch and push. User pre-authorized
   `git push --force` for dependabot branches specifically.
3. Charybdis repo only allows squash merge — discovered when `gh pr merge --auto --rebase`
   returned GraphQL "Merge method rebase merging is not allowed". Must check merge method
   settings before batch auto-merge.
4. After rebasing a PR that touched pixi.lock, `pyproject.toml` conflict resolution changed
   the dependency graph. The pixi.lock SHA no longer matched. `pixi install --locked` failed
   in CI. Always run `pixi lock` (not `pixi install`) after any pixi.lock rebase.

