**Changed by:** Mnemosyne 38-PR rebase session — CI fix rollout and conflict resolution patterns
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added trigger #25 (renumbered from old #25 in description): new CI job blocking all open PRs
  due to pre-existing violations (markdownlint/pixi-check on .claude/plugins/)
- Added trigger #26: two PRs independently amend same skill to same version with different
  content — treat as additive conflict, merge both sets of learnings, close redundant PR
- Added trigger #27: stale CI results requiring push to trigger fresh run
- Added 3 new "When to Use" bullets for all 3 patterns
- Added 3 new Failed Attempts rows:
  - Rebasing skill PRs when new CI job has pre-existing violations
  - Using git rebase --skip for superseded skill amendments without pushing
  - Auto-merge --rebase when repo only allows squash
- Added Quick Reference commands for all 3 patterns:
  - Check repo merge settings before auto-merge
  - Fix new CI job on main first, then rebase all PRs
