## v2.9.0 (2026-04-25) — Amendment 2 (ProjectTelemachy git hygiene session)

**Changed by:** ProjectTelemachy git hygiene pass — rebase branches, clean worktrees, fix PRs (2026-04-25)
**Verification:** unverified (observed Safety Net behavior and git cherry false-positive; not executed in CI)

### What changed (Amendment 2)
- Added trigger (24) to description and "When to Use" bullet: worktrees with modified pyc/__pycache__ or pixi.lock artifacts blocking rebase — both `git checkout --` and `git restore` are blocked by Safety Net; `git stash` is the only agent-safe path
- Added new "When to Use" bullet: `git cherry origin/main HEAD` shows `+` for a commit believed to be merged — cross-check with file-level `diff` before concluding work is unique
- Added 3 new Failed Attempts rows:
  - `git -C <wt> checkout -- <file>` to discard artifact changes → Safety Net blocks it; use `git stash` + `git stash drop` instead
  - `git -C <wt> restore <file>` to discard artifacts → Safety Net also blocks `git restore`; same stash workaround applies
  - `git cherry origin/main HEAD` false positive on `b8d40f3` dependabot config commit → patch-id is context-sensitive; always cross-check with `diff <(git show <sha>:<file>) <(git show origin/main:<file>)` for content identity

### Why (Amendment 2)
During the ProjectTelemachy git hygiene session, worktrees had modified pyc/__pycache__ and pixi.lock files (build artifacts, not real work). Attempts to discard them using `git checkout --` and `git restore` both failed — Safety Net blocks both commands. The workaround is `git stash` to park all dirty files before rebase, then `git stash drop` after. Additionally, `git cherry origin/main HEAD` reported `+` for a dependabot config commit that was identical to what was on main — the false positive occurred because surrounding lines in pixi.toml differed (pytest-cov and yamllint had been added), changing the patch context.

